description: Bring the superb flavours of Thai green curry to succulent chargrilled chicken kebabs. Try this easy recipe for a flavour-filled, no-fuss dinner.
keywords: Skewer & kebab,Quick & easy dinner,Quick & easy lunch,Dinner Made Easy,Chicken
name: Speedy Thai Green Curry Chicken Kebabs Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 800g chicken thigh fillets, cut into 3cm pieces
105g Five Tastes Thai green curry paste
450g SunRice microwave jasmine fragrant white rice
1 long red chill, thinly sliced (to serve)

recipeInstructions.text: Place chicken, paste and oil in a large bowl and stir to coat. Thread chicken onto 8 large metal skewers. Heat a large chargrill pan over high heat. Cook chicken skewers, turning, for 12 minutes or until browned and cooked through.
Meanwhile, heat rice according to packet instructions.
Make salad according to packet instructions.
Divide rice, salad and chicken skewers among serving plates. Serve scattered with coriander and chilli.
